posts.title: I did the math on the "missing" votes from 2020. All enclosed.
posts.content:
I took some liberties here but I tried to get as close as possible. Everyone by now has seen the chart where the 2020 election looks even fishier given the 2024 numbers. So I decided to do the math and find out where exactly the differences were. I only went down to the state level. If I didn't have a full time job I might go down to the district level given how interesting the state level findings are (not what I expected). At the end I will link my spreadsheet so you can check for yourself.

Taking a few liberties here, which are that some states are only showing as 95% on AP so there may still be some votes to be counted or cheated or whatever. Also while I was able to use the official election results from the FEC for 2020 I had to choose a legacy media outlet for the 2024 results. I chose NYT because it was the easiest to get data from, but they capped my view limit so I switched to AP. I noticed AP and NYT differ by ~5-6 votes so I went with the AP numbers for everything for consistency. These numbers are current as of posting this.

The total number of "missing" votes from 2020 is 13,687,488, or about 4.52% of the entire vote.

The 10 States with the largest % difference, put another way the states with the biggest decrease in turnout:

----Coming soon when CA and the other retarded West Coast states get >90% reporting. How can they take this fucking long?! It just doesn't make sense to post it when 40% of CA alone isn't included in the numbers. ---

The Swing State Verdict:

  1. PA - 13,991 FEWER votes in the 2024 election, .1% DECREASE in turnout.
  2. MI - 93,913 MORE votes in 2024 election, .84% INCREASE in turnout
  3. WI - 116,321 MORE votes in 2024 election, 1.73% INCREASE in turnout
  4. GA - 242,978 MORE votes in 2024 election, 2.37% INCREASE in turnout
  5. NV - 6,842 MORE votes in 2024 election, .24% INCREASE in turnout
  6. AZ* - 746,293 FEWER votes in 2924 election, 12.38% DECREASE in turnout (*AZ only reporting 76%)
  7. NC - 105,972 MORE votes in 2024 election, .95% INCREASE in turnout

Based on this list and with the data currently available it does NOT appear like the swing states are where the majority of the "missing" votes came from. Only PA and AZ* have fewer total votes than 2020. The rest of the swing states actually had increased participation in their elections.

So where did the missing votes go?

Well CA and WA are the major outliers. Keep in mind CA is only at 59% reporting which is pitiful but their turnout is trending down almost 20%. WA has counted 86% of it's votes and the out is down almost 12%. You would think these states are largely irrelevant when discussing the missing votes from the stolen 2020 election, but it's possible that Dems used their own lax rules in blue states to pad the vote totals and make small strategic adds to swing states look like blips.

The majority of states saw decreased turnout over 2020. A total of 36 states saw lower turnout than 2020, including large states like FL, PA, NY and IL. TX's turnout was roughly flat, within .08% of 2020 totals.

Many of the remaining states that saw increases in turnout are mass exodus states. People move there from hellholes like CA. Examples: TX, NV, NC, ID, GA.

Based on these early figures, which I will update later on, it appears like the decrease in turnout is spread among many states, but mostly blue states. CA, AK, UT, AZ, WA, OR, MS, DC, MD, IL, CO, HI, NJ, NY, MA, LA, KS, WV, CT, NE, OH, and IN all had 2% or more decrease in turnout.

The decrease was not concentrated in the swing states like I suspected and hypothesized. It seems more likely that swing states were strategically targeted by bad actors in 2020 and to cover that up many states, maybe all blue States, were also targeted with fraud to ensure that the vote totals didn't look out of place across the board. This prevents a scenario like the one I expected to see when I started this: aberrant vote totals primarily in swing states and not other states.

The numbers from 2020 are even less believable because the country was going through the covid hoax at the time. The idea that people would turnout to vote in such overwhelming numbers during a supposed pandemic stretches the limits of belief. The mail-in crap from 2020 is likely one of the primary origins of fraud, with Dems using databases to apply for mail in ballots and complete them for people unlikely to vote on their own. They could easily do this in blue states to pad the vote totals because those states have bad election security. Then they found clever ways to strategically add mail ballots to swing states to achieve a "victory" but not make it look like there were millions of extra swing state voters than there are.

Spreadsheet Link: https://file.io/ZpHRb9o2gUjU
